OL,3,CBaby suffered head injury when pram
OL,4,Crolled into 35mph train, report
OL,6,FThe pram rolled downhill towards the
OL,7,Fplatform edge and hit the train,
OL,8,Fresulting in the baby falling out and
OL,9,Fsuffering a minor head injury.
OL,11,FThe RAIB said: "RAIB has been unable
OL,12,Fto determine why the infant's parent
OL,13,Fmomentarily let go of the unbraked
OL,14,Fpram.
OL,16,F"The small degree of slope present is
OL,17,Funlikely to have been apparent to the
OL,18,Finfant's parent, who possibly became
OL,19,Fmomentarily distracted while unaware
OL,20,Fof the hazard created by the slope."
